data.title: Quick lunch was unexpectedly good
data.text:
I stopped for a quick lunch yesterday.  The owner, Katina, was very pleasant and the food was great.  I will be back.

One suggestion is to improve the exterior signage.  It doesn't reflect the good things inside.

data.title: Amazing baked goods, a must visit downtown Duluth!
data.text: The workers are very nice, fast service.  Their caramel rolls and cinnamon rolls and muffins are really good, I have gotten those multiple times.  But my ultimate favorite is their scones.  They have fruit scones and savory scones! Best scones in Duluth for sure, I definitely recommend going there.  They fresh bake everything each morning, so everything you are eating is fresh that day.

data.title: Seriously Overrated
data.text: Scones dry, breakfast sandwiches mostly bun and with funny pre-made eggs, bready cinnamon rolls,  quiche microwaved resulting in a wet crust...  Our group in its entirety found the food lacking.  Won't go back.

data.title: Such amazing baked goods
data.text: I don't actually drink coffee, but my husband tells me the coffee is great, too. But the scones... Wow. You can practically taste the cream and the sugar crust with the liberal supply of fruit that changes every day makes it an excellent way to start the day. Don't miss this place.

data.title: Absolutely delicious!
data.text: I had the triple-berry scone and fell in love! I am googling the recipe everywhere hoping to be able to make these when I return home! The coffee was so fresh and the employees are so sweet! They have a large variety of breakfast items and you will NOT be disappointed!

data.title: Amazing mini-cinnis
data.text: Arrived late in the day during the Tall Ships Festival. They were sold out of many of the offerings, but I got the last mini-cinni, and it was fantastic! So glad we pushed to arrive before she closed. Well worth the trip!

data.title: Excellent Baked Goods
data.text: Stopped there twice on our trip and really enjoyed the baked goods. The cinnamon rolls, caramel rolls and the cream cheese rolls were excellent. The house roasted coffee was good as well. I will definitely go back next time I am in Duluth.

data.title: delicious mini-cinni rolls and fresh coffee
data.text: Comfortable seating inside and right by an outside public seating area. The girl helping the people in front of me was a little rude to and impatient with them (they were having trouble deciding and had a lot of questions, but still...her attitude was uncalled for) but the guy who helped me was very nice. I had a breakfast sandwich that was freshly made and very yummy and took coffee and a mini cinnamon roll (honestly, not super-"mini"--it was the size of a small cinnamon roll, not bite-sized or anything like that) to go. The mini-cinni was SO GOOD, y'all. And for only $1.25, I highly recommend you try one. I'm sorry I only bought one for myself, as I could have eaten at least 6.

data.title: Loved the breakfast
data.text: I went to this little cafe for breakfast.  It opens early and it was so much cheaper than the restaurant in the hotel.  The quiche was incredible and so was the fresh cinnamon roll.  It's also an easy walk from the downtown hotels.

data.title: Mixed feelings
data.text:
Stopped here for the first time for breakfast.  My wife has a gluten sensitivity and other reviews I had seen mentioned gluten free options. That was not entirely accurate, as there gluten free options are only available if you pre-order for an event. 

The raspberry cheesecake roll I had was delicious, but the barrista was less than helpful and didn't really seem like she wanted to be there. We probably won't be back.

data.title: Mini cinnamon buns!
data.text: We actually stopped in for lunch but they didn't have much for lunch options that day so we settled for a treat and ventured on for lunch.  The salted caramel brownie was good but the mini cinnamon bun was amazing.  So yummy!  I'll definitely stop back in the future.  Such a cute atmosphere inside too.

data.title: Finally!
data.text: Finally a great little bakery! I ordered 2 cinnamon rolls, 2 chocolate chip cookies and a peach muffin to go....all items were delicious!!! Great job!!!

data.title: Mini cinis and Tanzanian Peaberry Coffee
data.text: I had to wait downtown for 45 minutes and this is the perfect spot!  We visit all the time on workdays and it is always busy, so the quiet Saturday morning was very different.  I usually have one of the fresh scones, but today the mini cinnamon rolls were calling me.  Yummy!

data.title: Go here instead of starbucks
data.text: This is a cute little cafe, with great coffee, and even better baked goods. The scones are all good, and my favorite thing was the salted caramel brownie. There's nothing fancy about this place, but everything is good, so you won't leave disappointed.

user_location.name: New York, New York, United States

data.title: New Local Bakehouse
data.text: What a GEM this little Bakehouse is... A new Local Business and they make everything from fresh local fair when possible.. Try a scone and a Latte' .. best I've ever had.... give it a try if you are in the Downtown area..

data.title: Get the Scone!!!!
data.text: Stopped by during a Duluth visit and remembered how talked up the scones were.  I had the Blueberry Scone which lived up to all the talk!!!  However, we also had the Mini-Cini Buns and they were good, but just not the best, could use a bit more time in the oven and more cinnamon and frosting.  The brewed coffee was very good and hot!  I would stop in here again when in Duluth, for a scone for sure and to give the Cinnamon Buns another try.  Great Staff too!:)

data.title: Delicious freshly baked scone
data.text: I went for coffee break and enjoyed a delicious freshly baked raspberry scone and hot tea.  Very nice and friendly atmosphere.

data.title: Quaint bakery/coffee shop downtown historic Duluth
data.text: This is a little coffee shop/bakery in downtown historic Duluth with delicious bakery and coffee, and helpful staff.  My sister-in-law and I walked several blocks in chilly November weather with the breeze coming off Lake Superior, and it was perfect atmosphere to walk into this quaint little shop and have a fun conversation with the barista.  Delicious bakery options. I had the baked oatmeal with berries and it was gluten free! And really good coffee and a fun place to take a rest and enjoy.

data.title: Absolutely Amazing
data.text: My family and I ordered  caramel rolls and raspberry cream cheese rolls.  They were delicious!  The best we have ever had!  Highly recommend this place!  Don't hesitate.... get here now!

data.title: Nice Cafe
data.text: The breakfast menu is delicious, the lunch menu (wraps, sandwiches) is okay. Fortunately they serve breakfast all day, so even at lunch time you can get a delicious egg sandwich. The atmosphere is nice and the staff is friendly.
